  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Time to intubate, view to glottic opening and success rate are not different when Airtraq
      technique is used compared to standard direct laryngoscopy in children.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      50 children (age 5 years and 11 month or younger) with expected easy intubation, scheduled
      for elective surgery requiring endotracheal intubation are enrolled.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
